{"type":"message","id":"9fccc9dd","parentId":"b7aa9363","timestamp":"2026-03-19T08:10:05.359Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a heartbeat/cron trigger for the context manager. Let me check the HEARTBEAT.md file to see what needs to be done.","thinkingSignature":"e276de9a2855972c20187c45ff44602fc1fa45a48e068d635bbf9eeec89e5ffe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g1y8ysli590o_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\HEARTBEAT.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":64,"output":72,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":37104,"totalTokens":37240,"cost":{"input":0.0000192,"output":0.0000864,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.00445248,"total":0.00455808}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773907800361}}
{"type":"message","id":"37002212","parentId":"9fccc9dd","timestamp":"2026-03-19T08:10:05.366Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_g1y8ysli590o_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# HEARTBEAT.md\n\n# Keep this file empty (or with only comments) to skip heartbeat API calls.\n\n# Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n\n## Context Manager Check\n\n- Run session_status to check current context usage\n- If context > 60%, consider saving memory and preparing for session switch\n- Check ~/proactivity/session-state.md for active tasks\n- Update ~/proactivity/memory/working-buffer.md if needed\n\n## Self-Improving Check\n\n- Read ./skills/self-improving/heartbeat-rules.md\n- Use ~/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md for last-run markers and action notes\n- If no file inside ~/self-improving/ changed since the last reviewed change, return HEARTBEAT_OK\n\n## Proactivity Check\n\n- Read ~/proactivity/heartbeat.md\n- Re-check active blockers, promised follow-ups, stale work, and missing decisions\n- Ask what useful check-in or next move would help right now\n- Message the user only when something changed or needs a decision\n- Update ~/proactivity/session-state.md after meaningful follow-through\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773907805364}}
{"type":"message","id":"404b0fe7","parentId":"37002212","timestamp":"2026-03-19T08:10:10.863Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to run through the heartbeat checks as specified in HEARTBEAT.md. Let me do them in order:\n\n1. Context Manager Check - run session_status, check context usage\n2. Self-Improving Check - read heartbeat-rules and heartbeat-state\n3. Proactivity Check - read heartbeat.md\n\nLet me start by running session_status and reading the relevant files.","thinkingSignature":"38d1575095323a117753e51e9d2fbac8fe4c6b7a7b0091842c1bc3ce6d1b8351"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ypedh7ltxhf1_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ypedh7ltxhf1_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\self-improving\\heartbeat-rules.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ypedh7ltxhf1_3","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\self-improving\\heartbeat-state.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ypedh7ltxhf1_4","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\proactivity\\heartbeat.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":483,"output":206,"cacheRead":37002,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37691,"cost":{"input":0.0001449,"output":0.0002472,"cacheRead":0.00111006,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00150216}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773907805366}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd805644","parentId":"404b0fe7","timestamp":"2026-03-19T08:10:11.155Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ypedh7ltxhf1_1","toolName":"session_status","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a)\n🕒 Time: Thursday, March 19th, 2026 — 16:10 (Asia/Shanghai)\n🧠 Model: minimax/MiniMax-M2.5 · 🔑 api-key (minimax:cn)\n🧮 Tokens: 64 in / 95 out · 💵 Cost: $0.0001\n🗄️ Cache: 100% hit · 37k cached, 102 new\n📚 Context: 41k/200k (21%) · 🧹 Compactions: 0\n📊 Usage: 5h 13% left ⏱3h 49m\n🧵 Session: agent:main:cron:696799cb-400f-4ac4-9393-6c861584965d • updated just now\n⚙️ Runtime: direct · Think: off · elevated\n🪢 Queue: collect (depth 0)"}],"details":{"ok":true,"sessionKey":"agent:main:cron:696799cb-400f-4ac4-9393-6c861584965d","changedModel":false,"statusText":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a)\n🕒 Time: Thursday, March 19th, 2026 — 16:10 (Asia/Shanghai)\n🧠 Model: minimax/MiniMax-M2.5 · 🔑 api-key (minimax:cn)\n🧮 Tokens: 64 in / 95 out · 💵 Cost: $0.0001\n🗄️ Cache: 100% hit · 37k cached, 102 new\n📚 Context: 41k/200k (21%) · 🧹 Compactions: 0\n📊 Usage: 5h 13% left ⏱3h 49m\n🧵 Session: agent:main:cron:696799cb-400f-4ac4-9393-6c861584965d • updated just now\n⚙️ Runtime: direct · Think: off · elevated\n🪢 Queue: collect (depth 0)"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773907811153}}
{"type":"message","id":"7263a75d","parentId":"cd805644","timestamp":"2026-03-19T08:10:11.156Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ypedh7ltxhf1_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Heartbeat Rules\r\n\r\nUse heartbeat to keep `~/self-improving/` organized without creating churn or losing data.\r\n\r\n## Source of Truth\r\n\r\nKeep the workspace `HEARTBEAT.md` snippet minimal.\r\nTreat this file as the stable contract for self-improving heartbeat behavior.\r\nStore mutable run state only in `~/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md`.\r\n\r\n## Start of Every Heartbeat\r\n\r\n1. Ensure `~/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md` exists.\r\n2. Write `last_heartbeat_started_at` immediately in ISO 8601.\r\n3. Read the previous `last_reviewed_change_at`.\r\n4. Scan `~/self-improving/` for files changed after that moment, excluding `heartbeat-state.md` itself.\r\n\r\n## If Nothing Changed\r\n\r\n- Set `last_heartbeat_result: HEARTBEAT_OK`\r\n- Append a short \"no material change\" note if you keep an action log\r\n- Return `HEARTBEAT_OK`\r\n\r\n## If Something Changed\r\n\r\nOnly do conservative organization:\r\n\r\n- refresh `index.md` if counts or file references drift\r\n- compact oversized files by merging duplicates or summarizing repetitive entries\r\n- move clearly misplaced notes to the right namespace only when the target is unambiguous\r\n- preserve confirmed rules and explicit corrections exactly\r\n- update `last_reviewed_change_at` only after the review finishes cleanly\r\n\r\n## Safety Rules\r\n\r\n- Most heartbeat runs should do nothing\r\n- Prefer append, summarize, or index fixes over large rewrites\r\n- Never delete data, empty files, or overwrite uncertain text\r\n- Never reorganize files outside `~/self-improving/`\r\n- If scope is ambiguous, leave files untouched and record a suggested follow-up instead\r\n\r\n## State Fields\r\n\r\nKeep `~/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md` simple:\r\n\r\n- `last_heartbeat_started_at`\r\n- `last_reviewed_change_at`\r\n- `last_heartbeat_result`\r\n- `last_actions`\r\n\r\n## Behavior Standard\r\n\r\nHeartbeat exists to keep the memory system tidy and trustworthy.\r\nIf no rule is clearly violated, do nothing.\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773907811155}}
